  <Docs since="18">
    <summary>This class represents a Trigger Event - the event
 associated with a Trigger Sensor.</summary>
    <remarks>
      <para tool="javadoc-to-mdoc">This class represents a Trigger Event - the event
 associated with a Trigger Sensor. When the sensor detects a trigger
 event condition, such as significant motion in the case of the
 <c><see cref="!:Android.Hardware.Sensor.TYPE_SIGNIFICANT_MOTION" /></c>, the <c><see cref="T:Android.Hardware.TriggerEventListener" /></c>
 is called with the TriggerEvent. The sensor is automatically canceled
 after the trigger.
 </para>
      <para tool="javadoc-to-mdoc">
 This class holds information such as the value of the sensor
 when the trigger happened, the timestamp along with detailed
 information regarding the Sensor itself.
 <format type="text/html"><h5 class="jd-tagtitle">See Also</h5></format><list type="bullet"><item><term><c><see cref="T:Android.Hardware.SensorManager" /></c></term></item><item><term><c><see cref="T:Android.Hardware.TriggerEvent" /></c></term></item><item><term><c><see cref="T:Android.Hardware.Sensor" /></c></term></item></list></para>
      <para tool="javadoc-to-mdoc">
        <format type="text/html">
          <a href="http://developer.android.com/reference/android/hardware/TriggerEvent.html" target="_blank">[Android Documentation]</a>
        </format>
      </para>
    </remarks>
    <since version="Added in API level 18" />
  </Docs>
